{"parse":{"title":"Singleton (lifestyle)","pageid":35253163,"revid":839621880,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p>\"<b>Singleton</b>\" is a term for human beings who live in a single-person household, especially those who prefer the lifestyle of living alone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup> It was popularized by the <i><a href=\"/wiki/Bridget_Jones\" title=\"Bridget Jones\">Bridget Jones</a></i> novels and films,<sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-8\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-8\">&#91;8&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-9\">&#91;9&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-10\">&#91;10&#93;</a></sup> but is also a term used in sociology. \n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Patterns\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Patterns</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#See_also\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">See also</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Patterns\">Patterns</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Singleton_(lifestyle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Patterns\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<p>Sociologist Eric Klinenberg reports that before the 1950s, no society has had large numbers of people living alone. Historically, this has happened when elderly people outlive their spouses, and when men have migrated for work.  In modern times, large numbers of people have begun to live happily alone in cities and with the help of communication technologies like the <a href=\"/wiki/Telephone\" title=\"Telephone\">telephone</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Email\" title=\"Email\">email</a>, and <a href=\"/wiki/Social_networking_service\" title=\"Social networking service\">social networking services</a>. Klinenberg has found that the ability of women to work, own property, and initiate divorce creates more opportunities for living alone; in countries like <a href=\"/wiki/Saudi_Arabia\" title=\"Saudi Arabia\">Saudi Arabia</a> where women do not have autonomy, relatively few  people live alone.<sup id=\"cite_ref-11\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-11\">&#91;11&#93;</a></sup>\n</p><p><a href=\"/wiki/Single_people\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Single people\">Single people</a> may live alone before their first romantic partner, after a divorce, or after their partner has died. When unmarried or married <a href=\"/wiki/Couple_(relationship)\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Couple (relationship)\">couples</a> maintain separate residences as an alternative to <a href=\"/wiki/Cohabitation\" title=\"Cohabitation\">cohabitation</a>, it may be a <a href=\"/wiki/Long_distance_relationship\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Long distance relationship\">long distance relationship</a>, a temporary separation due to troubles in the relationship, or simply <a href=\"/wiki/Living_apart_together\" title=\"Living apart together\">living apart together</a>.\n</p>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"See_also\">See also</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Singleton_(lifestyle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: See also\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li><a href=\"/wiki/Hipster_(contemporary_subculture)\" title=\"Hipster (contemporary subculture)\">Hipster</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Living_apart_together\" title=\"Living apart together\">Living apart together</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Recluse\" title=\"Recluse\">Recluse</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Sloane_Ranger\" title=\"Sloane Ranger\">Sloane Ranger</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Single_person\" title=\"Single person\">Single person</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Yuppie\" title=\"Yuppie\">Yuppie</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"/wiki/Young_professional\" title=\"Young professional\">Young professional</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Singleton_(lifestyle)&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap mw-references-columns\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https: